
[1]mortality

   MORTAL'ITY, n. [L. mortalitas.] Subjection to death or the necessity of
   dying.

   When I saw her die,

   I then did think on your mortality.

   1. Death.

   Gladly would I meet

   Mortality, my sentence.

   2. Frequency of death; actual death of great numbers of men or beasts;
   as a time of great mortality.

   3. Human nature.

   Take these tears, mortality's relief.

   4. Power of destruction.

   Mortality and mercy in Vienna,

   Live in thy tongue and heart.
